# Vue SFC — BEM and scoped SCSS

This rule covers **CSS class naming** and **`<style lang="scss">`** only. It does not cover `data-test-*` template hooks (see [vue-template-test-hooks.mdc](vue-template-test-hooks.mdc)) or `<script setup>` structure (see [vue-quasar.mdc](vue-quasar.mdc)).

## Block and element classes (template)

Follow components such as [GlobalWindowButtons.vue](src/components/globals/GlobalWindowButtons/GlobalWindowButtons.vue) and [AppControlMenus.vue](src/components/globals/AppControlMenus/AppControlMenus.vue):

- **Block**: one root class per component, lowerCamelCase (e.g. `globalWindowButtons`, `appControlMenus`).
- **Elements**: `blockName__element` (double underscore), e.g. `globalWindowButtons__button`, `globalWindowButtons__minimize`, `appControlMenus__inner`.
- **Quasar / utilities**: keep existing Quasar props and utility classes (`flat`, `bg-dark`, etc.) on the same nodes when the codebase already combines them with BEM classes.

Use **HTML comments** in the template to group sections (buttons, tooltips, regions) the way existing components do.

## Scoped SCSS

- Prefer `<style lang="scss" scoped>` unless unscoped styles are intentional for that file (match neighboring components in the feature).
- Do **not** introduce new raw **colors** or **sized units** (`px`, `rem`, `vh`, etc.) in component SCSS when they belong in the shared catalogue. Add or reuse variables in [quasar.variables.scss](src/css/quasar.variables.scss) under the correct section (see [project-scss.mdc](project-scss.mdc)). Catalogue variables use **hyphens** between name segments (never underscores in `$` identifiers). This rule applies to `<style>` blocks only, not to template attributes or prop strings unless policy expands.
- Do **not** use **framework palette** Sass variables (`$primary`, `$grey`, `$white`, `$dark`, `$accent`, …) directly in component SCSS. Add a **semantic** token in the catalogue and reference that — same indirection as for raw sizes and hex (see [project-scss.mdc](project-scss.mdc) **Palette variables vs semantic color tokens**). Prefer reusing existing semantic Globals (e.g. `$aLinkColor`) when they match the role.
- Nest element rules under the block with the parent selector:

```scss
.appControlMenus {
  &__inner {
    -webkit-app-region: no-drag;
  }
}
```

- Avoid deep nesting; prefer extra element classes over long compound selectors.

## Global / shared styles

Cross-app SCSS lives under [src/css](src/css) — see [project-scss.mdc](project-scss.mdc). Component-specific BEM stays in the SFC **or**, when an external sheet is required (usually for SFC size), under that feature’s **`styles/`** folder — see [component-styles-folder.mdc](component-styles-folder.mdc).

## TypeScript interfaces and types (`types/`)

- Put shared `interface` / `type` declarations in repository-root `types/` (import with `app/types/...`). Prefer one domain-oriented module per feature area with brief JSDoc on exports (see `types/I_appMenusDataList.ts`). Do not add colocated `<filename>.types.ts` under `src/`, `src-electron/`, or `.storybook-workspace/`. Ambient augmentations for third-party modules also live under `types/` and are loaded with a side-effect import from the owning boot file or `src/stores/index.ts` (see `types/piniaModuleAugmentation.ts`).
- For JavaScript (`.js`), TypeScript (`.ts`), Vue (`.vue`), and JSON (`.json`, `.jsonc`, `.json5`) files, enforce expanded multi-line object literals via ESLint (`object-curly-newline` + `object-property-newline`) and keep files auto-fixable with `eslint --fix`.
